The TTL countdown procedure is supposed to be followed only for cached
data, and not for the delegation data or the glue  RRs.  I know of no
BIND version that follows the spec, and some versions are incompatible
with others.

At present, only type A RRs make sense for glue.  Other types may be
relevant in the future.

paul

